[b]S/R Zones MTF v2[/b] builds multi-timeframe support and resistance zones directly from ATR-reversal structure swings — not from arbitrary lookbacks or pivot counts, but from the points where price actually reversed relative to volatility.

[b]What it does[/b]

For each configured timeframe, the script identifies swing highs and lows where the reversal exceeded an ATR-based threshold. These become zone boundaries. Zones from multiple timeframes are overlaid on the chart, scored for strength, and merged when they overlap — reducing clutter and surfacing the levels that matter most.

[b]Features[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Multi-timeframe[/b] — Up to two higher timeframes plus the chart timeframe, all configurable
[*][b]ATR-based construction[/b] — Zone boundaries derived from volatility-relative reversals, not fixed pivot counts
[*][b]Zone merging[/b] — Overlapping zones across timeframes are combined into single, stronger levels
[*][b]Zone scoring[/b] — Each zone is scored based on the strength and quality of the reversal that created it
[*][b]Display limit[/b] — Configurable maximum zone count keeps the chart readable
[/list]

